Fire story:
The innovator IBM enters into its second century of its existence
If you are looking for a suitable word that the strategy of IBM most closely, then this would be the word "longevity."
For the general public, IBM is synonymous with technological revolution, we know it as a modern company, even though a century has passed since its inception.
The basis for this longevity has been its first chief - the visionary Thomas J. Watson,.
He was the slogan, countless global problems could easily solved if people would be willing to think a little bit.
His slogan "Think!" has become the hallmark, which should take the life of the future giant (and, at the same time, the title of the company's internal magazine, IBM in the year 1935 began).
This was also the basis of the Watsen thoroughly prepared corporate culture.
"For us from IBM means that long-term thinking is a kontinuelle movement towards the future.
IBM survived and was also an entire century successful because it has remained true to its principles and not shied away changing everything else around it.
This allowed us, in the course of our first century, the technology to transform the business and society.
We hope that we will create even more in the next hundred years, "said Samuel J. Palmisano, the current director of the company on the occasion of the anniversary.
Thought-out system
Watson was already in the 1930s social care of its employees - in a similar way, as the entrepreneurs Baťa in Czechoslovakia: IBM people had as one of the first American workers paid holidays, an insurance through the entrepreneurs, plus elegant uniforms and working clothes and a reasonable salary system for best innovators and traders.
Equally sophisticated IBM long-term relationships with their customers.
The company was brilliant from the outset in the promotion of talent - as one of the first companies worldwide, IBM any discrimination - and could pick and choose accordingly.
