The railway has mapped out a crisis plan, which is to prevent Zugausfälle in winter.
The number of staff should be doubled.
It will cost millions.
In the fight against winterbedingte Zugausfälle and delays, the Deutsche Bahn, according to a newspaper report this year, more than 70 million.
The "picture" newspaper reported earlier, citing a company internal krisen plan, by 2015, investments by a total of around EUR 300 million.
This should be achieved a better availability of vehicles and rail network in extreme Witterungen.
Is planned, among other things, a doubling of the internal and external staff for snow removal on rail facilities and rail increase to 16000 people.
The aim is to train up to the start of the year and 90 percent of the necessary choices within four to five hours of snow and ice.
Two months ago, rail chief Rudiger pit after a top-level meeting with government and industry Zugausfalls and delays in this winter.
Last winter, the railway passenger transport significant problems, since it has, among other things, difficult weather conditions, a lack of reserves.
So many new regional trains have been waiting for years for a licence from the Federal Railway Administration.
In addition, there is a delay in the extradition of ICE-Zugs.
The railway also makes for years to create that they are axes of ICE trains significantly more frequently in the workshop, after an ICE in Cologne Central Station had axes.
