After the uproar over boss Josef Ackermann is new hardships from the United States: the Deutsche Bank must pay a million repentance.
As if the problems at home for the Deutsche Bank were not enough, the industry giants, now his past in the United States: the Frankfurt Institute pays in a comparison of $145 million (106 million euros) to settle disputes because of the collapse of five major cooperative banks during the financial crisis.
It is about the sale of mortgage securities.
The financial market regulator NCUA raises a whole series of big banks, cooperative banks with false promises to buy financial products; they have played down the risks.
Such papers lost during the financial crisis and the banks in depth.
"We are pleased that we have been able to resolve the issue without the parties had to go before the court," said a Deutsche Bank spokesman in New York.
The bank admitted no fault with the comparison.
This also applies to Citigroup, which has committed itself to the payment of 20.5 million dollars.
The NCUA chairman Debbie Matz welcomed the cooperation of the two houses.
The National Credit Union Administration (NCUA) is responsible for the banks and jumps in order to protect the customer deposits.
The NCUA is trying to get the billions of dollars of damage.
The now closed comparisons are the first of its kind.
The regulator had also attacked other big banks, and in the summer of JPMorgan Chase, the Royal Bank of Scotland and Goldman Sachs.
The questionable mortgage Securities in question are so-called mortgage backed Securities.
These loans are based.
When the housing bubble burst in 2007, it was a wide range of financial firms to the disaster.
