The Deutsche Bank also to a complaint from the FHFA, it is about several shops worth a total of $14.2 billion for the years 2005 to 2007.
The regulator demanded that the Frankfurt for "substantial losses ," without specifying an exact figure.
The Deutsche Bank had rejected the claims as unfounded and want to defend themselves.
Warren Buffett is rising with 10 billion in IBM
Financial guru Buffett invested heavily in IT companies IBM.
Since March he has bought in the value of more than 10 billion dollars.
So far, the great American investor Warren Buffett always said, not to invest in IT and computer companies, since the long-term development of the firms only bad forecast.
Now, however, he read the reports from IBM and changed his mind about investment in the industry.
He had much earlier must understand that IBM implied in particular services and computer systems for the IT departments of other companies.
An investment by Warren Buffett is regarded as a slap in the financial world.
As a result, the it primitive IBM now "Sir IBM."
Because Buffett revealed in the U.S. broadcaster CNBC that he bought since March IBM shares in the value of 10.7 billion dollars.
His investment holding company Berkshire Hathaway is one of the largest shareholders of IBM with a share of 5.5 percent.
Buffett said that not even IBM previously knew anything about the commitment.
He praised the management, even in the economic crisis had not yet provided for decent profits.
"You have done an excellent job," said Buffett, on the strategy.
IBM has for a long time on the lucrative IT services as the operation of data centres.
More than 100 years old computer pioneer also offers software and advice, as well as powerful corporate computers.
Buffett had shunned technology companies shunned until now.
He says he only invest in companies whose business he also understand.
Instead, Buffett, for example, in a freight train, a lubricant manufacturer or mechanical engineers.
His holding company Berkshire Hathaway owns alongside around 80 own subsidiaries also shares in a number of major corporations such as Coca-Cola or Munich Re, the former Munich back.
The 81 year-old person had developed in the 1960s, the small textile firm Berkshire Hathaway and with wise investment to one of the most valuable companies in the world.
However, is his modest lifestyle.
It is for many investors around the world, a cult figure.
His almost unmistakable sense for making money has given him the moniker "Oracle of Omaha."
After the announcement of Buffett investments, the IBM-Aktie vorbörslich rose by one percent.
"Big Blue ," as IBM is known, is in the stock market as a whole, more than $220 billion worth and counts along with Apple and Microsoft, the most valuable technology companies in the world.
In the case of Microsoft, Buffett said, but he did not want to their own.
Founder Bill Gates is a close friend.
