ADB urges Asia to help in the rescue of the euro zone
The Asian Development Bank (Asian Development Bank ADB) calls on India and China to support the rescue of the euro zone in its heavy debt crisis, in order to prevent a long-term downward trend, which will slow down the growth of the economy in Asia.
Rajat Nag, administrative director of the ADB headquarters in Manila, said that the two fastest growing economies in the world "must do" everything in your power to the recovery of the currency bloc, either by the International Monetary Fund to speed up or through direct mutual agreements.
He warned of the BRIC countries (Brazil, Russia, India, China), the "dispassionately" look at the difficulties in Europe, and said that the financial support of the European leadership and European resources through Asia to prevent a long-term collapse of the global economy.
"We are all in the same boat."
"So everyone is helpful, which can help Europe out of this crisis," he told the Financial Times in an interview on the sidelines of the World Economic Forum in Mumbai.
"Asia may be protected to a certain extent, but it is not immune."
"If China and India can help, then by all means."
Europe's monetary union was in the past few months in a severe debt crisis.
In the last few days, Italy rose dangerously interest costs, and the Prime Minister, both Italy and Greece have resigned.
The heavy debt crisis in Europe is fuelling fears that the global economy could plunge into recession and led to calls, the leading emerging countries must unite to support the euro zone.
Mr Nag said that any support in Asia will be channelled through the IMF, but said that mutual agreements - such as the purchase of bonds of the EU rescue fund, the European Financial Stability Facility (EFSF) - the European partners in Asia, greater bargaining power.
Anand Sharma, the Indian trade minister, said that "India will do everything in its power" to help the euro zone, as the domestic economy is suffering from falling exports and the drying up of foreign capital flows.
"No one wants to see that the euro zone remains unstable and turbulent," he said.
"We are facing great challenges and we need to maintain a high growth level."
"It is not an option, it is a task, because where else we find work for our millions of young men and women."
Others argue that emerging economies such as India have no reason to help the rich Europeans, even if they are facing major economic challenges.
Ashutosh Varshney, a professor at American Brown University, said that it would be politically very difficult to sell the 1.2 billion people in India, aid for Europe, of which more than 800 million of $2 or less a day.
"At some point they will find that the Greeks with 50 retire and holidays are on the beach, and then you have a problem," he said.
Lee Howell, executive director of the World Economic Forum, asked why India's reserves should be used in Greece, the numerous and well paid employees to keep in the public sector, with jobs in bad geleitetet losses einbringe nden institutions such as the railways.
Mr. Nag said that the crises in the euro zone "significant knock-on effects" on the whole of Asia.
The ADB forecast an economic growth at 7.5 percent in Asia for the years 2011 / now threatens "the risk of escalation," because of the threat from Europe.
He said that vulnerable emerging markets must "contingency plans" to prepare themselves for a downward trend and a significant outflow of capital Wortschaften.
Urgent warnings from the Pentagon against possible cuts in the defence
Secretary of Defense Leon Panetta fueled the Congress on Monday, when he warned that automatic budget cuts would weaken national security unnoticed, so he set off a financial chain reaction from the halls of the Pentagon to the chessboards in Afghanistan and civilian conveyor belts.
The Pentagon already rethinking cuts of $450 trillion dollars over the next decade, but now fears that further cuts 600 trillion or more will be needed if the Congress can reach a conclusion in the spending.
"The impact of these cuts would be devastating for the ministry," Panetta wrote in a letter to the Republican Senators John McCain, Arizona, and Lindsey Graham, South Carolina.
He said that a failure of the Congress in reaching a budget agreement, which will lead to a so-called seizure, would lead to 23% across-the-board cuts, as well as a halt numerous new projects.
"Such a large cut, carried out in such a way that would make most of our shipping and construction projects unfeasible - you cannot buy three quarters of a ship or a building - and other modernization efforts seriously harm," Panetta wrote to the senators.
"We would be forced to separate us involuntarily from a large part of our civilian personnel and, since the reduction would be implemented quickly, we would have almost certainly kinds of civilians, in order to be able to achieve the goal."
"These changes would destroy the faith of those who maintain our military and our alert seriously damage."
The cuts were in the end, the combat troops, "said Panetta.
"During the war time quotas in the fight against terror are not directly affected by the seizure, the serious interference would adversely affect the war effort in the budget," Panetta warned.
"Recruitment has been cut, leading to delays in the recruitment and hiring supervision, support the war."
"The salaries of the staff would be cut, which leads to late payments to dealers and the legal and political support would be disrupted."
The two senators said Panetta 10 days ago and asked for further details regarding the potential influence of the automatic cuts to the Ministry of defence.
"The consequences of a seizure of the Ministry of Defence would be a rapid decline in the United States as the leading military power in the world."
"We are vehemently opposed to this draconian action," the senators said in a joint statement on Monday afternoon, when she Panettas letter published.
"This is a result that we cannot live with, and it is certainly not one that we should impose."
"The seizure is a threat to national security interests of the United States and their commitment should not be allowed."
Whether Panettas letter and the new warnings of the senators will increase the pressure on a compromise in the budget or will strengthen demands to exempt the Pentagon from cuts remains to be seen.
Panetta has become increasingly outspoken about the possible cuts, although he has many years of experience with the budget in Congress and the White House, before he came to the top of the Pentagon, and knows that he faces difficult choices.
At a press conference in the last week, the defence minister, painting a gloomy picture, which could face a military shell, but without a core.
"It is a ship without sailors."
"It is a brigade without ammunition."
"It is an air Force squadrons without sufficient trained pilots."
"It is a paper tiger, an army barracks, buildings and bombs without adequately trained soldiers who are able to fulfil the mission," Panetta said in his opening speech at the Pentagon.
"It is a force, there is a lack of morality and alert, and is not in a position to compete with potential opponents."
"You can be angry."
In an annex to his letters to McCain and Graham, Panetta new details of how reductions "creates significant operational risks: delays in times of crisis, conflicts and disasters, serious restrictions on our global commitment and response capacity, which leads to an unacceptable risk in future military operations."
And Panetta said that some of the removal of the largest defense projects could fall victim, including those who have already been tested and are already in the early stage of planning.
This list also includes Fighter planes F35 Joint Strike Fighter, a planned new aircraft bombs, the next generation of ballistic submarines, the new litt oral combat Ship and the new ground combat vehicle, the Army and Navy need to replace the Humvee.
We would stop the further development and testing of the F35, it would in the next 10 years to save up to 80 trillion dollars, but supporters say that it can be an important next step in the buildup, so that the possible dangers posed by China and other opponents.
As a lie unmasks
A glance at the current headlines shows how serious and widespread deception and lies in daily life.
The Republican presidential nominee for president, Herman Cain, is dealing with the allegations of sexual harassment on the part of several women. Both sides accuse each other of lying.
The leadership of Penh State is accused of the President's, since it has allegedly withheld reports, according to which a retired football coach boy sexually abused.
In the past week has been mitangehört on an open microphone, as the French President Nicolas Sarkozy, the American President Barack Obama, the Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is a liar.
Lies destroy careers and shake countries.
The New York congressman and Internetexhibitionist Anthony Weidner was kidding when he brought renunciations in circulation, which were quickly refuted by incontrovertible evidence.
The former presidential candidate John Edwards is accused of violations in the campaign financing in connection with the cover-up of an extramarital affair.
And then, of course, no one forgets that it has seen the media circus, President Bill Clinton has triggered when he during his second term in the Oval Office about his sexual relationship with Monica Lewinsky lied.
Stories about Schummeln at school and college tests are widespread.
There have been incidents in which teachers their students test answers, so that they themselves well in their performance reviews.
Mentors, who should teach the opposite, send a message that lies and Schummeln.
How much deception we see?
As studies show that we are lying every day between 10 and 200 times.
Many of these lies, but as Notlügen.
Another study shows that strangers to each other three times during the first 10 minutes of a meeting.
Lies, or "lies" is one that is important for every human being, and that both personal and professional reasons.
Far from a parlor game such as, for example, in which it is the goal, "you!" is the Enttarnen of a deception, a serious knowledge based on scientific data over the past six decades have been collected at prestigious universities, which had carried out extensive research projects, particularly in the fields of psychology and physiology.
As a result of the research is that most of the old myths about the lies were revealed.
Look lies in the eye.
They stammeln falters, blush and zappeln not always.
As a result, we can not conclude that these liars difficult to identify and treat.
An experienced Lügenenttarner can penetrate the truth, something about the structure of the opinion that the subtle facial expressions, and timing.
I have spent several years, the scientific findings of the comprehensive and steadily growing area of the in exposing, and it is clear that the Enttarnen of a deception is a modern ability, which is easy to learn and help us find in our complex world, especially if the closing or the questioning of people or negotiations or administration belong to their own professional responsibilities.
Good liars are very good to other people to raise their interest and to control their own emotions. And they intuitively sense how they are perceived by others.
Thanks to the research, we know that extrovertierte people are more often than introvertierte people that men are more than women, "lies" selbstorientierte whose lies more "other" - usually they want to protect the feelings of others - that married people anlügen their partners less often than unmarried people (but the lies they tell are mostly "fat lies ").
We also know that if a person has been exposed as a culprit, others feel less guilty, this person to have lied.
As you can tell whether someone is lying?
First, by watching the normal behaviour of this person.
This is called "Baselining," the starting position.
It is a point of reference for the subsequent assessment of changes.
A the attitude, the laughter, the quality of their participants.
They should know better, when someone is normally standing trippelt with the foot, so that they do not unfairly when he trippelt during a meeting with the foot.
Then you look at accumulations more startling verbal and nonverbaler behaviour.
Consider these accumulations as alarm bells ring, not as proof of an exposing.
People who are, perhaps, if they try to remember their history, and perhaps their feet in the door or they are in the outcome, change their position on significant way or show a "relaxation after the recruitment interview," this deep, entspannende Ausatmen and the change in attitude, if all the hard questions are over.
Interrogator often mistakenly signal that a recruitment conversation is over, only after this detente after the recruitment interview.
You also pay attention to the language of your participants.
The slip-up by Scott Peterson is famous, when he used the past tense, when he claimed that his wife was still on life and triggered a national search for her.
Deceptive individuals can also use a distance language: "I have not had a sexual relationship with this woman... Miss Lewinsky" or if you have a tricky question repeated in its entirety.
The most frequent verbal signs are subtle.
Some people use "qualifying language" when it is a vexed question: ..." in order to tell you the truth... As far as I know... In good faith. "
This is the answer wahrnehmend rather than factual, which often the alarm bells.
There is no magic remedy for Enttarnen of lies, but they can learn skills, thanks to an exposing is possible.
Thanks to these skills can be the victims of fraudsters, both in private and professional life.
