The court approved for 2015, the transition to digital television in Mexico
The switchover from analogue to digital signals in the world in recent years, the most important changes.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN), the constitutional claims, which the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies were lodged against the presidential decree, and the switch from analogue to digital signals must be brought forward from 2021 to 2015, due to a lack of eight votes are needed for the legal challenge.
A minority of four ministers, including the President of the Supreme Court, Juan Silva Meza, was of the opinion that the President Felipe Calderón has not exceeded his powers when he decree-law with the details of the switch to the terrestrial digital television.
With this decision was rejected by the Senate's constitutional dispute, because he did not have the necessary qualified majority of eight votes, so that the court could decide the constitutionality or the constitutionality. So the law remains in force.
In the project for the complaint, which the Minister Olga Sanchez Cordero has been proposed to explain the decree law unconstitutional because, for the radio and television regulations affecting the Comisión Federal de Telecomunicaciones (Cofetel) (Federale telecommunications Commission in Mexico) is responsible, which is why the decree-law hierarchical principles and the law would contradict.
In favour of the project, only Zaldivar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies constitutional complaints against the decree-law. After the adoption of the complaints, the Minister Sánchez Cordero decree-law no longer and all activities to create the digital transmission.
The Council of Ministers also rejected the complaint filed by the Chamber of Deputies, without entering into the debate on the project, for which the Minister Sánchez Cordero was responsible.
In his speech, the Prime Minister, not to agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the national government is not with the general provisions of the measures, which should take the public administration must regulate.
"I do not believe that, if we were to do, that would undermine the independence of the regulator." you recalled that the planning of strategic policy areas, such as the telecommunications sector, the central state government is responsible for constitutional reasons, because it is the state affairs.
The replacement of analogue signals by digital is one of the most important changes that have taken place in recent years around the world, and it leads to a better use of the elektrischen spectrum, a higher quality of the signal and more channels.
The delay in the changeover, she said, was a postponement of the gain of digitisation, which is a decision in the public interest, not just a technical point of view, "because they include economic, social, political and security aspects."
These matters, she said, "the action of the entire system, in accordance with the principle of economic management by the state had a group of characteristics, which the Constitution in the hands of the central government."
She called that many countries around the world, the digital conversion have already carried out, and the government, even though they have highly specialised facilities.
It could not conclude that the government with the publication of the contested law decree in the powers of the Congress, because the laws passed by the legislature would be respected, "he said.
The possibility of the ballots in Michoacán individual auszuzählen will be considered
According to the information provided by PREP, the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor just 27 percent, with 879 votes from a total of 6074 have not yet been counted.
The possibility of individual counting of the ballots in this year's elections in Michoacán a reality, because the Preliminares oral Programa de Resultados Electorales Preliminares (PREP) issued data is the difference between the first and second place in the gubernatorial elections nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes not yet counted a total yet been counted.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that just adopted last November 9, the election of a series of regulations on the harmonisation of local rules with the reforms of the federal states in Electoral matters.
It should be remembered that Michoacán neither his political constitution nor his electoral law nor its law on the election of justice had adapted to the reforms adopted by Congress, so that they in this round were in force, but the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided their publication in the Gazette within the deadlines with the argument that have any objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) on the constitutional complaint filed by the local legislature and, the voice of the State Ombudsman on the constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal" because it does not have the right to "decide or a veto against it."
María de los Ángeles Llanderal said in an interview about the possibility of a single count of the votes that, thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM now the possibility that the local election authority, the ballot papers partially or completely auszählen.
Under the following conditions in one or more electoral packages contained votes will be counted partial results in the protocols do not agree; the protocol on the counting of and calculation is not an excessive or it is not in possession of the chairman of the electoral commission or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total count of the total ausgefüllten ballot papers will be carried out if there is a difference between the presumed winner and the second place is the same or less than one percent, provided at the beginning of the session is an explicit request from the party or coalition chairman, the second of the candidates.
The counting of votes can also be carried out in its entirety, if it is after completion of the proper calculation that the difference between the presumed winner and the candidate on the second place equal to or less than one percent, provided that there is an explicit request from a representative of the party, whose candidate has become the second. In this case, the election packages were exposed to a partial recount were excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia in the same situation, where, according to PREP the difference between the first and second place just under 0.16%, even though the votes of 129 of a total of 923 election protocols have not yet been counted.
