"To play in Costa Rica is a dream come true."
In an exclusive interview with Viva says the Bassist Jeff Ament of Pearl Jam, the band is prepared for the next Sunday in the national stadium to give one of their best concerts.
More than 20 years they have been expected, but the band assured that it is a dream come true, if they play in Costa Rica.
The the Bassist and Mitgründer group, Jeff Ament, the Viva last week by Brazil from an exclusive interview.
The band is in the South American part of their tour to celebrate their 20 years of existence, and on Sunday, 20, they make their only freeze in Central America.
On this day, they come from 7.30 pm in the national stadium, along with the band the X from Los Angeles and Las robe rtas from Costa Rica.
They read an excerpt from the conversation, the full transcript to be found in the online edition of La Nación.
For your Costa Rican fans realised a dream when Pearl Jam plays in Costa Rica: Are you aware of what this means for your fans?
To play in Costa Rica is a dream come true for us.
This is just the second time that we in South and Central America, and until now, it has been great.
I am only on holiday in Costa Rica. It is a beautiful country, that we will stay a few days ago.
