MSS announces a research protocol for the location of the gene for obesity in
Social Security Institution, Mexico's leading a research project for the location of the gene for obesity among children and young people, which will be supported by specialists of the IPN.
The Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social - IMSS (Social Security Institution of Mexico) announced that a research project on the discovery of the gene for obesity among children and young people under the title "genetics of obesity in childhood and youth," with which the genetic markers associated with obesity are to be.
Miguel Cruz López, head of the Unidad de Investigación Médica en Bioquímica (department for medical research, focus biochemistry) at the clinic Hospital de Especialidades del Centro Médico Nacional Siglo XXI stated that a multidisciplinary team consisting of doctors, health workers, food specialists and social workers.
This team will be supported by specialists and students of the postgraduate degree course at the Instituto Nacional de Salud Pública (INSP) and Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados (Cinvestav) del Instituto Politécnico Nacional (IPN).
The public is invited to take part in the study. Interested parties can come to the sports fields of the IMSS in the Valley of Mexico, where every Saturday from 8.00 am tests with children and young people.
He stressed that the investigation on the sports ground of Cuauhtémoc (in the west of the state México) began since 8 October at the sports ground of Nezahualcóyolt (in the east of the Federal state México) will continue.
If the goal of 500 to 600 individuals is achieved, the study on the sports ground of Independencia (in the south of the main urban bezirks) continued and Morelos (in the north of the main urban bezirks).
He said that the aim of the study is the understanding of the factors and the role of genetics in connection with the development of obesity and the identification of risk factors of Mexican children and young people to the prevention of chronic degenerative diseases.
On the occasion of the global day of diabetes, he said it would seek three thousand children and young people aged from six to 14 years with the consent and under the supervision of their parents should fill nutritional questionnaires.
They are also questions about their physical activity and their family illness history, risk factors, diabetes or renal insufficiency, to control.
He also led to the aforementioned Samstags investigative subjects measured (weight, size, Taillenumfang), controlled their blood pressure and blood values such as the glucose levels, Triglyceride, Cholesterol, insulin and genetic factors (attempt to identify genes associated with obesity in childhood).
Cruz López stressed that the investigation would take advantage of the health workers concerned about the alarming weight of young people.
"The health surveys from the years 1999 and 2006 showed that in less than six years, the proportion of obese boys 77 percent and the girls with obesity had increased by 47%, while obesity has risen dramatically," said the expert of the IMSS.
He admitted that the search for genetic markers was justified because the genetic history of Mexico's population of the differences in other nations.
He admitted that a (e) Mexicans (in) to 65% on average indianisch American, European and 30 to 5 percent of African descent in the genes, which is associated with diabetes and obesity,.
More generally, he said, the genetics of obesity in the inability to burn the surplus of energy (calories) burned, so that this will be stored in the form of fat.
The researchers said that the direct benefits for the research participants would be in a comprehensive study of the children, which would determine whether they had a degree of obesity or obesity.
It would even the appearance of dark skin wrinkles in the neck and arm of the Innenarm (Akanthosis) on the likelihood of metabolic disorders and diabetes at the preliminary stage.
All the information would be kept confidential and told the parents in writing by the doctors. The doctors say parents all measurements and propose lifestyle changes, which are for the prevention of diseases.
Cruz López said that there would be three basic factors that are responsible for obesity, obesity and other chronic diseases: lack of exercise, the lack of movement on a daily basis, most of the time of the day in front of the television and means of transport to go, rather than short routes.
The high caloric intake, which means an increased consumption of gezuckerten drinks and Kohlenhydraten (Tamales, bread, pizza, hamburgers, etc.), along with a high fat and protein, as well as genetics, which is to be analysed in this research project.
Asphalt from the UNAM prevents potholes
Rafael Herrera, researchers at the School of Chemistry in the Mexican University UNAM developed with Polymeren modified Asphalte to mix more resistant to weather conditions and temperature fluctuations
The which stem from the road surface, respected, it would not be required to repair nearly 200 000 potholes, when the rainy season in the Zona Metropolitana del Valle de México (city area of the valley of Mexico) breaks out, said Rafael Herrera Nájera, researchers at the School of Chemistry (FQ) at the University of UNAM, warning and assured that if the laying and maintenance of the Asphaltbelags happen, the number of potholes significantly reduced or avoided altogether.
"Potholes from a technical point of view," he in his speech on the occasion of the International Year of Chemistry, he announced that the laboratory, for which he is responsible, with Polymeren modified Asphalte was developing, in a similar mixture, but the asphalt mechanical resistance in both high and low temperatures.
Herrera Nájera said that this type of modified Asphalte in areas with extremely hot climate, such as, for example, in some cities in the north of the country, should be used to improve the behaviour of the road surface and to avoid the appearance of blow holes.
He said that the asphalt - the hardest part of oil - a hydrocarbon link, which is part of a high molecular weight - the so-called Asphaltene - and the other part of a low - the so-called Malthene. Together they give the road surface his characteristic zähelastisches behavior.
Zähelastisches behavior Asphalts means that this high temperatures of nearly 180 °C behaves like a liquid at 120 ° C, it is very liquid and 50 ° C, while he is fragile at very low temperatures.
"This means that the resilience of the asphalt is not uniform on the streets, but on a day in accordance with the changing weather conditions and temperature fluctuations," said the chemical engineer.
The researchers said the FQ, the streets of Mexico City would have a majority of a flexible road surface, which is composed of six layers of material, which included the last three asphalt.
Between the upper classes is a wear layer of asphalt, which is made up of small and then solidified stones bathed in asphalt.
Each piece this decay class, was bathed in asphalt.
If the vehicles to move and forces produced this situation is a good distribution of forces in the road surface.
"If it is modified asphalt, the forces would be even better," said the chemical engineer.
"The erosion," he said, "is being interpreted in a recent class, the so-called Tragschicht, which consists of tiny stones, from sand, which was also in asphalt.
Since this situation in contact with the car tyres, they need greater mechanical strength than the wear layer and they must produce friction.
The road surface receives the most forces and distributed, the Tragschicht also needs an appropriate thickness and the material from which it must be maintained.
The weather conditions, especially humidity and temperature fluctuations, are more important to take into account factors, above all, the water, "he said," because it affects the behaviour of the wear layer.
If the site is damp, water in the class and only difficult, and this is a dilution of all sections of the road surface and as a result, the incidence of stroke holes.
If a pothole, "he said," will initially cover layer worn out, while the wear layer that will be affected, but the damage is not immediately, but it is a process that the first signs of adequate maintenance programmes should be maintained. "
The member of the Sistema Nacional de Investigadores (National research system Mexico) said that the burden of another important reason for the appearance of blow holes. It is therefore crucial that the thickness of each layer of the surface is always in relation to the vehicle and it must be ensured that frequent potholes with this rule will be met.
Rafael Herrera pointed out that many research to achieve Asphaltemulsionen, for example, which in other countries are already on the market, and with which the bumps simply and without application of high temperatures.
