Anti-Islamic crimes and offences have increased by 50%
The directed against Muslims crimes and offences have increased from 2009 to 2010 by 50%, whereas other racially or religiously motivated crimes of violence, according to the FBI statistics published on Monday in the same period either slightly decreased or increased slightly.
According to this data is the total number of violent crimes committed against Muslims from 107 in 2009 to 160 in 2010, has risen by 49%, whereas a 13% increase in the number of acts of violence against Catholics, a 4% drop in crimes against Jews, as well as a global increase of 14% of religious crimes and offences.
The total number of "hate crimes" in a very weak Maβe 6628 cases, including 47.3% racial differences and 20% motivated by religious differences crimes, such as the FBI.
"After a slowdown in 2009, it is disturbing that these crimes and offences will grow again," said the human rights organisation human rights First, "the rise of anti-Islamic violence is particularly significant," the organisation added in a statement.
"Human rights First, had been stressed that the violence directed against Muslims, as well as all forms of hate crimes as a serious infringement of human rights should be considered," added Paul Legendre, a representative of the organisation.
"The American government can and should do more to combat these attacks," he added under assessment that this improvement in the police attitude towards the "hate crimes" could be carried out.
The "hate crimes" is in the U.S. federal law as a legacy from the era of the struggle for civil rights.
This legislation was adopted after the death of Martin Luther King, in order to punish acts of violence directed against race, colour, religion or ethnic origin, and now also offences of sexual identity.
