"Contact" smart cards will be introduced
The world fair opens for smart cards on Tuesday in Villepinte near Paris optimistic attitude in their doors.
The year 2011, according to the smart with a 11% increase in worldwide sales of Mikroprozessorchips (debit cards, SIM cards), with more than 6 billion units sold.
The tragendste segment is the to contact free technology payments on public transport or settling purchases by simply keeping the card to a reading device.
Compared with a year earlier sold 320 million this year, 460 million contact smart cards will be sold worldwide.
Its market share should increase further (580 million expected units) and more than 10% of the global smart card market (6.925 million cards) to in 2012.
Europe wins in terms of contactless payment to land after a long time in the Asia Pacific region is behind hergehinkt.
Some 26 million Visa cards are already equipped with this functionality, and 75,000 payment terminals accept them.
In France, the beginnings are modest: only 400,000 kontaktlose Visa cards have been distributed.
However, the consumer markets make steam.
Carrefour has therefore issued this year, 2.5 million contact passport master cards.
In order to move to higher speed, it is necessary for the banks to provide their customers with these cards.
"Two major French financial institutions have committed themselves to their customers in future to systematically bank cards, which are drawn up with kontaktlosem chip," announces Gérard Nébouy, Director General of France.
Banks test payment via mobile phone
However, this is only a first step on the road to the medium of the future: the mobile phone.
A tiny percentage of equipment is so far with the implementation of these transactions necessary NFC technology (Near Field Communication).
"You are in default."
"But they should at least next year a real upward trend."
"We expect in 2012 with the sale of 80 to 120 million units worldwide," said Marc Bertin, chairman of the smart.
But the banks take initiative.
The Crédit Agricole announced the launch of a Testlaufes in Caen, which will take place from December until next June.
The iPhones of some 200 customers and staff are to be fitted with a contact.
The BPCE is conducting a similar project in Strasbourg and Marseille.
And the Société Générale had testified yesterday to prepare for the market introduction of an offer to their customers kontaktlose payment by mobile phone.
